    <title>The Open Technology Institute endorses the Battle of the Mesh v6</title>
    <link>http://commotionwireless.net/fr/blog/open-technology-institute-endorses-battle-mesh-v6</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt; &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; id=&quot;internal-source-marker_0.19396559966617988&quot;&gt;Since 2009, wireless mesh enthusiasts and community networking activists from across the globe have come together for a tournament of a social nature: &lt;a href=&quot;http://battlemesh.org/&quot;&gt;&quot;Wireless Battle of the Mesh&quot;&lt;/a&gt;. Each battle is held in a different European location, creating a unique series of testbeds for this band of hacktivists and wireless innovators to examine the performance of the various mesh data routing protocols.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
